\id 1CO – ATV, Plain English Version 
\h 1 Corinthians 
\toc3 1 Corinthians 
\toc2 1 Corinthians 
\toc1 Paul’s 1st Letter to the Corinthians 
\mt1 The 1st letter that Paul wrote to the Christians at Corinth  
\mt2 (The book in the Holy Bible called \bk 1 Corinthians\bk*)  
\imt1 About this letter  
\ip Paul wrote this letter about 2,000 years ago, about 20 years after Jesus went back to heaven. It is now in the Holy Bible.  
\ip Paul wrote this letter to the Christians that were living in the city called Corinth, in the country we now call Greece, where Greek people come from. A big earthquake knocked that city down more than 160 years ago, so the Greek people built a new town about 3 kilometres away and called it Corinth. That town is still there today.  
\ip At the time when Paul wrote this letter, Corinth had 2 harbours for ships, and those ships brought a lot of things to Corinth. A lot of people bought things and sold those things there, to get money for themselves. There were also a lot of people there that did bad things to get money.  
\ip Paul went to Corinth to tell the people there about Jesus, and he stayed there teaching them for about a year and a half (see Acts 18:1-18). Some of the Corinth people believed Paul’s message and became Christians.  
\ip Then Paul went to other places. But the Christians at Corinth started to have some problems. So they wrote a letter to Paul and asked him some questions. Then Paul wrote this letter to answer those questions, and to tell them the right way for Christians to live.  
\ip This letter has a lot of good messages for Christians today. Paul wrote it to help the Christians in Corinth live the right way, and it can help us work out the right way to live too.  
\cl Chapter  
\c 1  
\p
